                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "Hey, I work on this - Alexey has a good read on the aims and scope of the protocol.\n\nSome thoughts:\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "[Different implementations of blocks] can potentially fragment the ecosystem, so iiuc they plan to spec this as well"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "We’re conscious of multiple implementation approaches potentially leading to fragmentation, with React-implemented blocks limited to applications who are happy to ship React, and other variations.\n\nIt’s a tricky balance to strike between freedom for the block author (i.e. can they implement it how they want, or must they use X) and work for the embedding application (how many different flavours of block implementation do they need to deal with - albeit we can provide libraries for this to save every application rolling their own).\n\n"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_quote",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " The spec also does not define how blocks are distributed, how end users can search or add them"
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "type": "rich_text_section",
                        "elements": [
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": "The spec does not define this, and I’m not sure we want to require that people use particular distribution methods, but we do provide one - "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/blockprotocol.org\/docs\/publishing-blocks#block-hub",
                                "text": "at a very early, too-manual stage"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " - and have "
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "link",
                                "url": "https:\/\/blockprotocol.org\/docs\/embedding-blocks#discovering-blocks",
                                "text": "an API"
                            },
                            {
                                "type": "text",
                                "text": " which allows callers to filter blocks by keywords, or by data structure (i.e. pass a data structure and you will be returned blocks which have a schema compatible with that data structure)."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ],
